result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan J. Peebles was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Ryan J. Peebles is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Ryan J. Peebles was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Ryan J. Peebles was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Early termination after 22 months if all costs are paid and no violations of probation. 66 days sentence credit if revoked.

miscConds.notes: Costs Payable to DOC. Defendant is to pay $20/month starting 1/1/23.

The Defendant is to complete an AODA assessment and comply/continue with any treatment recommended. The Defendant is to undergo any counseling the agent finds appropriate and must comply with any recommended treatment/assessment/counseling.  Defendant may not withdraw from any ordered program without permission of the agent and/or provider. The Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - no alcohol or drugs unless prescribed by a physician. Defendant must obtain and maintain employment/educational programming/counseling. The Defendant is to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis by 12/1/22, unless already provided. If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due, and/or other collection means, such as income assignment will be issued.
